    "slug": "10-design-tips-for-awesome-nonprofit-online-presentations",
    "link": "https://www.nptechforgood.com/2020/12/13/10-design-tips-for-awesome-nonprofit-online-presentations/",
    "title": {
      "rendered": "10 Design Tips for Awesome Nonprofit Online Presentations"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p>By <span style=\"color: #3b78dd;\"><a style=\"color: #3b78dd;\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/bethsinger1/\"><strong>Beth Singer</strong></a></span>, Principal at <span style=\"color: #3b78dd;\"><a style=\"color: #3b78dd;\" href=\"https://www.bethsingerdesign.com/\"> <strong>Beth Singer Design, LLC</strong></a></span> \u2013 a design and communications firm specializing in nonprofit organizations to help them fundraise, educate, and promote membership and the mission of their institutions though design solutions.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Calling all presenters, trainers, and fundraisers!</strong></p>\n<p>With the crazy number of online meetings we all have these days, you are probably assembling a toolbox with new ways to communicate. Enter an old friend: the slide deck. These have been around for ages, but you may not have used them as if your organization\u2019s mission depended on them. Now, more than ever before, we need to secure the attention and devotion of our colleagues, most important donors, and supporters. And we need tools that are effective and easy to produce so we can keep our connections fluid, generate enthusiasm for our ideas, and open new doors.</p>\n<p>Crafting a kick-ass online presentation can help ensure that your most important contacts are still in your court. If produced with clarity and passion, your presentation will show respect for those in attendance, thought leadership, and pride in your message and your organization. A combination of lucidity, persuasiveness, and great design will create a compelling experience for participants.</p>\n<p><strong>Here are 10 tips for making your next presentation your best presentation!</strong></p>\n<h2><strong>1) Timing</strong></h2>\n<p>Organize your content so that you change slides every 7 to 15 seconds. Your presentation should be visually stimulating and provide succinct content. The longer you keep a slide on screen, the greater the chance of losing your audience\u2019s attention \u2014 no matter how good a speaker you might be.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.bethsingerdesign.com/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-28036 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-1.jpg?resize=960%2C540\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-1.jpg?w=960&amp;ssl=1 960w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-1.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-1.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /></a></p>\n<h2><strong>2) Design</strong></h2>\n<p>The most appealing presentations don\u2019t just have good grammar and nice pictures; they are beautifully designed. Just as with a well-written essay, a thoughtful structure and a polished style will help your ideas shine through. When you employ design excellence, you show your audience that you have carefully considered what you want to say and how to say it.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.slideshare.net/BethSinger1/aarp-pitch-deck\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-28037 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-2.jpg?resize=720%2C540\" alt=\"\" width=\"720\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-2.jpg?w=720&amp;ssl=1 720w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-2.jpg?resize=300%2C225&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px\" /></a></p>\n<h2><strong>3) First slide</strong></h2>\n<p>Your opening slide will set the tone and, just as with people, that first impression is critical. The first slide may be on screen for several minutes before your presentation begins, so make sure that it conveys a sense of excitement, is true to your brand or mission, and carries one of your important messages.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www2.slideshare.net/BethSinger1/health-in-harmony-presentation-template\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-28039 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-3.jpg?resize=960%2C540\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-3.jpg?w=960&amp;ssl=1 960w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-3.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-3.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /></a></p>\n<h2><strong>4) Last slide</strong></h2>\n<p>Your last slide is equally important because it usually stays up after your talk is over. Use the last slide to encourage questions, cement a final message, give people contact information for email and social media, or as a final call to action.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.bethsingerdesign.com/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-28040 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-4.jpg?resize=720%2C540\" alt=\"\" width=\"720\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-4.jpg?w=720&amp;ssl=1 720w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-4.jpg?resize=300%2C225&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px\" /></a></p>\n<h2><strong>5) Divider slides</strong></h2>\n<p>Section openings have three important functions: 1) signaling your audience to pay extra attention because a new type of information is coming; 2) summarizing what you want them to remember about that section; and 3) offering a little break.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.slideshare.net/BethSinger1/aarp-pitch-deck\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-28043 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-5.jpg?resize=720%2C540\" alt=\"\" width=\"720\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-5.jpg?w=720&amp;ssl=1 720w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-5.jpg?resize=300%2C225&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px\" /></a></p>\n<h2><strong>6) Brevity rules</strong></h2>\n<p>Be succinct: The less you have on a slide, the more your audience will remember. A good rule of thumb is to limit your content to two sentences per slide or four short bullets.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.slideshare.net/BethSinger1/aarp-pitch-deck\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-28044 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-6.jpg?resize=720%2C540\" alt=\"\" width=\"720\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-6.jpg?w=720&amp;ssl=1 720w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-6.jpg?resize=300%2C225&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px\" /></a></p>\n<h2><strong>7) Visual variety</strong></h2>\n<p>Use a variety of photos or illustrations \u2014 and use them frequently. Select photos that tell a story related to your content and avoid using them purely for decoration. Studies show that the human brain retains information more accurately and longer when a visual element reinforces a verbal presentation.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.bethsingerdesign.com/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-28046 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-7.jpg?resize=960%2C540\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-7.jpg?w=960&amp;ssl=1 960w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-7.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-7.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /></a></p>\n<p>You can also \u201cbuild\u201d your message so that each bullet point comes up in succession on one slide by making an animated gif. These are quite easy to do and will add variety and rhythm to your presentation.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.bethsingerdesign.com/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-28047 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-8.gif?resize=853%2C480\" alt=\"\" width=\"853\" height=\"480\" /></a></p>\n<h2><strong>8) Rhythm</strong></h2>\n<p>Pacing is important for engagement. Use a variety of approaches \u2014 some slides with text only, some with a balance of images and words, some with a dominant image, and use divider slides, where appropriate, to break up the presentation. Do not show the same kind of slide more than three times in a row, or you risk boring your viewers.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www2.slideshare.net/BethSinger1/aarp-pitch-deck\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-28137 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Slide-1.jpg?resize=720%2C540\" alt=\"\" width=\"720\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Slide-1.jpg?w=720&amp;ssl=1 720w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Slide-1.jpg?resize=300%2C225&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.slideshare.net/BethSinger1/aarp-pitch-deck\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-28052 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-9-1.jpg?resize=720%2C540\" alt=\"\" width=\"720\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-9-1.jpg?w=720&amp;ssl=1 720w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-9-1.jpg?resize=300%2C225&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.bethsingerdesign.com/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-28138 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Slide-2.jpg?resize=960%2C540\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Slide-2.jpg?w=960&amp;ssl=1 960w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Slide-2.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Slide-2.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /></a></p>\n<h2><strong>9) Data is very powerful</strong></h2>\n<p>DO include bar charts, pie charts, and diagrams if they support your points. DON\u2019T make them too complicated \u2014\u00a0they must be understood in a matter of seconds. Use your headline to explain what the data reveals and what you want your viewers to know.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.bethsingerdesign.com/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-28141 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Slide-4.jpg?resize=960%2C540\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Slide-4.jpg?w=960&amp;ssl=1 960w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Slide-4.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Slide-4.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.bethsingerdesign.com/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-28053 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-10.jpg?resize=960%2C540\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-10.jpg?w=960&amp;ssl=1 960w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-10.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-10.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-28140 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Slide-3.jpg?resize=960%2C540\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Slide-3.jpg?w=960&amp;ssl=1 960w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Slide-3.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Slide-3.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /></a></p>\n<h2><strong>10) Legibility</strong></h2>\n<p>Pay close attention to legibility. White or light-colored type on a dark background is the easiest to read because of the contrast. (That\u2019s why most highway signs are dark green with white letters.) A white or light background with dark type can also work well. Be sure to test for legibility on screens of different sizes \u2014 laptops, desktops, and tablets \u2014 to make sure your content can easily and quickly be read in all situations.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.bethsingerdesign.com/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-28054 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-11.jpg?resize=960%2C540\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-11.jpg?w=960&amp;ssl=1 960w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-11.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Nonprofit-Slide-11.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /></a></p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Have questions or need help with designing, editing, or writing your next presentation?</strong> <a href=\"https://www.bethsingerdesign.com/\"><strong><span style=\"color: #3b78dd;\">Beth Singer Design, LLC</span></strong></a> is a design and communications firm specializing in nonprofit organizations to help them fundraise, educate, and promote membership and the mission of their institutions though design solutions. Check out these full decks we wrote and designed for <span style=\"color: #3b78dd;\"><a style=\"color: #3b78dd;\" href=\"https://www.slideshare.net/BethSinger1/aarp-pitch-deck\"><strong>AARP</strong></a></span>, <strong><a href=\"https://www.slideshare.net/BethSinger1/health-in-harmony-presentation-template\"><span style=\"color: #3b78dd;\">Health in Harmony</span></a></strong>, and <span style=\"color: #3b78dd;\"><a style=\"color: #3b78dd;\" href=\"https://www.slideshare.net/BethSinger1/progressive-jewish-fund-presentation-231181251\"><strong>New Israel Fund</strong></a></span>.</p>\n",
